This paper is primarily focused on the computational complexity of the Boson Sampling problem, which is a topic in both quantum computing (cs.QU) and classical complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses algorithms and computational techniques, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.IT (information theory). Finally, the paper discusses experimental limitations of current photonic quantum computing, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.SD (systems and control).
